      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-08T17:59:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Agreed.",
      "parentUuid": "fdbdff68_9760e14d",
      "revId": "6fe748f566a1bd07b26011927e858d9e96db4bcb",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "bf23e7f1_7347a7e0",
        "filename": "resultdb/proto/rpc/v1/invocation.proto",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 131,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001907
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-08T18:00:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "My preference would be to export this to BQ specifically to AVOID people relying on the structure of the invocation ID; this field has documented structure, whereas, AFAIK, INVOCATION_ID does not.\n\nI don\u0027t think \"thousands of small strings\" is worthwhile to optimize out of BQ?\n\nSeparate CL is fine.",
      "parentUuid": "fdbdff68_9760e14d",
      "revId": "6fe748f566a1bd07b26011927e858d9e96db4bcb",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "416bad42_dff14c7d",
        "filename": "resultdb/proto/rpc/v1/invocation.proto",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 131,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001907
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-08T18:01:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Oh, maybe I misunderstood; Do we not have an invocation table, and so this data would be duplicated to every test result?\n\nIf so... can we have an invocation table instead? :)",
      "parentUuid": "bf23e7f1_7347a7e0",
      "revId": "6fe748f566a1bd07b26011927e858d9e96db4bcb",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6e20a35e_7a7bcd2d",
        "filename": "resultdb/proto/rpc/v1/invocation.proto",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 131,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-09T21:59:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "invocation name does have a documented structure for builds and tasks, but i agree that prepending \"https\" is way easier than regexing the invocation name. I am not sure we should be optimizing for this though. Yes, Chrome OS are building their UI with SQLs, which I find a bit weird, but they seem to be reaching the conclusion that this is a bad idea, so I am not sure we should try to solve \"generate URL\" problems in BigQuery.\n\nwe don\u0027t have an invocations table, as they are no use cases right now. Normally if someone wants to operate at the invocation level, it would be easier for them to use the producer resource\u0027s native table, e.g. swarming tasks table or buidbucket builds table.\n\nUltimately, I think this shouldn\u0027t be in this CL, but we can keep discussing this.",
      "parentUuid": "416bad42_dff14c7d",
      "revId": "6fe748f566a1bd07b26011927e858d9e96db4bcb",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "777dafc4_b4f94b37",
        "filename": "resultdb/proto/rpc/v1/invocation.proto",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 131,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001907
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-09T22:12:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "(agree not in this CL)\n\nI think we should provide data in the easiest way to digest, and I\u0027d prefer that data in the API is available in BQ, apart from some technical limitation (like it\u0027s too large or something like that). Regexes (or conditional parsing thingies) in the client aren\u0027t great, imo.",
      "parentUuid": "6e20a35e_7a7bcd2d",
      "revId": "6fe748f566a1bd07b26011927e858d9e96db4bcb",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "0c881794_22238283",
        "filename": "resultdb/proto/rpc/v1/invocation.proto",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 131,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-09T22:16:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "note that the BQ table today already doesn\u0027t provide everything that is available in RPCs.\n\nI agree that regexes in the client aren\u0027t great. But so is SQL for UI :) \n\n\u003e I think we should provide data in the easiest way to digest\n\ni think we should try to be a bit more pragmatic. Nobody is asking for this in BQ.",
      "parentUuid": "777dafc4_b4f94b37",
      "revId": "6fe748f566a1bd07b26011927e858d9e96db4bcb",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "031a3aa2_28e47b7d",
        "filename": "resultdb/proto/rpc/v1/invocation.proto",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 131,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001907
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-09T22:29:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "IMO the pragmatic thing to do is to include data parity by default, not to pick and choose without a concrete reason (like: this will cost millions of $ / second, or run us out of quota).\n\nPicking and choosing means that every time there\u0027s new data there\u0027s time wasted debating if it should be included, and then additional time wasted when someone finds out that its missing and has to ask around to figure out why (and then disappointment when the answer was \"well, we didn\u0027t feel like it\")",
      "parentUuid": "0c881794_22238283",
      "revId": "6fe748f566a1bd07b26011927e858d9e96db4bcb",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "16447749_7678b945",
        "filename": "resultdb/proto/rpc/v1/invocation.proto",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 131,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-09T22:39:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "concrete reason: we don\u0027t fully own schemas of these tables. In Buildbucket we do, because there is one table and we own its schema. Here we let the users to specify table name, so there is a lot of tables.\nThis means we have to think about schema migrations. BQ does not automatically create columns just because we sent values. This is not implemented yet and I don\u0027t see a strong reason to do it now. We have enough high priority work.\n\ni think the answer is not \"well, we didn\u0027t feel like it\" but we didn\u0027t have a use case. I think this is not as subjective, as you are making it sound.",
      "parentUuid": "031a3aa2_28e47b7d",
      "revId": "6fe748f566a1bd07b26011927e858d9e96db4bcb",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d8c50a16_56befd8b",
        "filename": "resultdb/proto/rpc/v1/invocation.proto",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 131,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001907
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-09T22:42:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think we\u0027ll have to agree to disagree then; I don\u0027t find this a compelling reason to let the schemas drift apart. It sounds either subjective (i.e. it\u0027s not actually that hard we just don\u0027t want to do it) or a design flaw (the tables are migration-proof).\n\nThe use case is so that we don\u0027t have documentation and implementations littered with context sensitive exceptions and caveats.",
      "parentUuid": "16447749_7678b945",
      "revId": "6fe748f566a1bd07b26011927e858d9e96db4bcb",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "cfb8ed88_b90f310e",
